winlsof — a memory-safe, Windows-native reimplementation of lsof
================================================================

This project is an original Rust reimplementation. It is *inspired by* and aims
for command-line / output compatibility with the lsof utility, but shares no
source code with it.

The original lsof was written by Victor A. Abell and is Copyright (c) 2002
Purdue Research Foundation. See ../COPYING in this repository for the original
lsof license. The behavioral specification this reimplementation targets is
derived from the original lsof documentation (../docs, ../Lsof.8) and its
observable behavior.

Windows API access is provided through the `windows` crate
(https://github.com/microsoft/windows-rs), Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation,
licensed under MIT/Apache-2.0.
